Good Morning ☀️🤍

Writing this feels like December 31st. i feel like we’ve lived a whole year and it’s only february. i’ve had some highs, 21 day fast with God and church, amazing new contracts, working in london, modeling in paris, evening out my anxiety with zoloft, my big chop, my first tattoo, etc. and some lows that showed me how there’s still more room to grow up and fully step into womanhood. i’m so grateful for all of you growing up with me. i’ve let go of so many excuses, 2023 is NO MORE EXCUSES. no more blaming things, people, or events i can’t control. this is my year of accountability and abundance as i fully step into my voice and my power. i don’t really know what is coming by december 31st fr but im in SHOCK at how much God can move me right and left in just 2 months, just get me where you need me. i’m really learning ME and i’m doing it in front of you, and that’s kinda scary. but whether im right or wrong, and sometimes i am wrong, i’ll always be true to me. and that’s my wish for you. be unapologetically you this year, even if shifts some tides. this has taught me the deepest form of self love. 🤍
CIAA 🏀

I finally went to Greece! 🇬🇷🤍 My southern european roots play a pretty big part of my DNA (Spain, 40%!) I had the honor of exploring my spanish roots in 2012. Now, exploring more of my mediterranean roots through the lens of our greek neighbors through culture, food, traditions, and faith has filled holes in my identity i’ve dreamt about since I was little. I can’t wait to keep exploring the regions that have made me, West Africa is next! It’s such a gift to get context of what i was taught about myself and actually get to live it. when you immerse yourself, something just *clicks* within you. Thank you God for completely paying for this trip (storytime soon) and covering me and my safety. 👼🏽 and for my dear friend and I who finally got our COVID trip and our new friends we’ve made along the way. 🫶🏾

I started swapping some of my favorite brands last year and here are three things i’ve learned:

1. Price points are often not as drastically different. The world of attainable ethical fashion is growing RAPIDLY, especially with many smaller brands starting to boom. they know your price concerns, and they’ve got you! 

2. the clothes don’t last just a few washes. i’ve found myself repeating outfits more often of my sustainable pieces, mainly because they feel better, and withhold the wash without losing integrity. 

3. it’s gonna be hard sometimes. we shouldn’t strive for perfection, but for progress. saying no to a piece you see on your favorite creator, unsubscribing to your fav store’s discount emails, and personally, not re-uping that 6 month content contract 😭 

these small swaps really create better habits and honestly save you money, and our earth, in the long run. to end: here are some ethical stores i’ve been enjoying, and the internet has been LOVING 🩷 : @whatlowants @girlfriend @parade @lovaeij @sotelaco @jessakae 

if you ever want to test your favorite brand, head to directory.goodonyou.eco to see their sustainability rating and transparency! and always, see if your favorite brand offers transparency directly on their site.

how many times have you heard the phrase “It’s not a diet, it’s a lifestyle change”? I used to think that people were gaslighting themselves, but I actually get it. you are not meant to be on an endless weight loss journey. I quit diet culture in 2021 after VSG and have been on a slow journey to heal my relationship with food. decrutching food after two years has been very up and down but this last shift has finally made “ eat what you love in moderation” CLICK for me. GRATEFUL to see what the scale will say but i’m not gonna look because it might trigger my obsessions again. this was about preparing for pregnancy and no birth control, but this was a wonderful side effect!!! #CleanEating
